<b>Guoray Cai</b> is an associate professor of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../485/9605485.xml">
College of Information Sciences and Technology</link> in <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../509/1209509.xml">
Pennsylvania State University</link></university>
, where he is also an affiliate faculty of Department of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../910/18963910.xml">
Geography</link> and an affiliate faculty of Department of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../425/524425.xml">
Computer Science and Engineering</link>. <p>

Cai has done research work  in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../398/12398.xml">
geographical information systems</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../516/13516.xml">
human-computer interaction</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link>, and geography of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../381/7381.xml">
cyberspace</link>. He has published works in international journals and conferences, such as Proceedings of IEEE, International Journal of Geographical Information Science, Transactions in GIS, Networks, Networks and Spatial Economics, and IEEE international conferences and Symposiums. </p>
<p>

He has been a paper reviewer for more than 10 journals in the field of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../398/12398.xml">
GIS</link>. <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> </p>

<sec>
<st>
 Research Activity </st>
<p>

Currently, he is in charge of four on-going <agency wordnetid="108337324" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../427/157427.xml">
National Science Foundation</link></agency>
 funding projects with total individual credit $405,521.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> Jorge Schement commented on his work of resource map system as "a real groundbreaker"<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref>
. His project, DAVE_G, was also reported by ACM Technews.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref></p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
 Awards </st>
<p>

He has been awarded a NASA Global Change Graduate Fellowship, the Allen Kent Award from <link>
University  of Pittsburgh</link>, and a presidential award from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../408/658408.xml">
Tianjin University</link></university>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../862/5042862.xml">
China</link>. <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%224%22])">4</ref></p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
 Career </st>
<p>

Cai received a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../916/530916.xml">
Bachelor of Engineering</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../789/999789.xml">
Master of Engineering</link> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../531/9531.xml">
Electrical Engineering</link> from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../408/658408.xml">
Tianjin University</link></university>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../862/5042862.xml">
China</link>, a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../896/4126896.xml">
Master of Arts</link> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../910/18963910.xml">
Geography</link> from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../979/185979.xml">
West Virginia University</link></university>
 in 1993, and a <degree wordnetid="105093890" confidence="0.8">
<property wordnetid="104916342" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/8775.xml">
Doctor of Philosophy</link></property>
</degree>
 in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../354/149354.xml">
Information Science</link> from the <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../870/239870.xml">
University of Pittsburgh</link></university>
 in 1999. Before Cai came to academia, he had  professional experience, including the NASA Global Change Program, USDA Forest Service, <division wordnetid="108220714" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_unit wordnetid="108077292" confidence="0.8">
<department wordnetid="108114861" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../350/1930350.xml">
Pennsylvania Department of Education</link></department>
</administrative_unit>
</division>
, and five years as a research scientist in <institute wordnetid="108407330" confidence="0.8">
<social_group wordnetid="107950920" confidence="0.8">
<society wordnetid="107966140" confidence="0.8">
<association wordnetid="108049401" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../856/377856.xml">
Chinese Academy of Sciences</link></group>
</association>
</society>
</social_group>
</institute>
. He is a faculty member in three departments in Pennsylvania State University. He also is an active member of <organization wordnetid="108008335" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../ury/30th_century.xml">
ACM</link></organization>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../938/56938.xml">
IEEE</link>, and ASPRS.
<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>

